parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The tailgate opening and closing on its own can cause safety risks, especially if it happens while driving, and can lead to loss of personal belongings.
symptoms: The tailgate opens and closes repeatedly
even when the remote control button is not pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The trunk opening while driving can cause personal belongings to be thrown out of the vehicle, creating a safety hazard and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: even when the trunk open switch or key fob button is not pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The complete shutdown of the electronic dashboard can cause the driver to lose critical information, such as speed, while driving, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The electronic dashboard completely shuts off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate display of speed and tachometer readings can cause the driver to lose critical information, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The digital image of the speedometer and tachometer needles shift to the left
making it impossible to accurately read the speed of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rearview camera can cause the driver to lose visibility while reversing, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The rearview camera display blacks out intermittently while reversing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the front sensors and headlights can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive in certain conditions, such as snow or darkness.
symptoms: The front sensors flash "trouble" on the dashboard
and ice forms over the sensors and headlights

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension and Steering System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension and steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Chassis Stabilization and Electronic Stability Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the chassis stabilization and electronic stability control system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seatbelt Restraint System and Airbag Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the seatbelt restraint system and airbag can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a collision.
The sudden shattering of the sunroof while driving can cause distraction, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents.
The trunk opening randomly while driving or parked can cause distraction, loss of control, and potentially lead to accidents or theft.
symptoms: sometimes while driving at low speeds
and the alarm may go off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Bluetooth system to notify the driver of new text messages can cause distraction, as the driver may attempt to check their phone while driving.
symptoms: The Bluetooth system does not notify the driver of new text messages while connected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blind spot detection system can increase the risk of accidents, as the driver may not be aware of vehicles in their blind spot.
symptoms: The blind spot detection system does not work consistently
failing to alert the driver of vehicles in their blind spot.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: even with the engagement of ABS and/or collision deterrent systems.
